diff_analysis.evidence: The patch adds CSRF protections and origin checks rather than removing them. For qute://settings, it introduces a per-session CSRF token checked on /set requests and blocks cross-origin or non-XHR attempts in both WebEngine and WebKit paths. No new XSS, ReDoS, code injection, or path traversal sinks are introduced; the file:// handler signature change only adds context parameters and does not weaken path handling. Overall, the new code reduces CSRF risk and does not introduce any of the listed CWEs.
